obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (3366)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes `1. 22nd July, 1950, vide notification No. S.R.O. 123, dated 22nd July, 1950, see Gazette of India, 1950, part II, s. 3.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00019_195040_1517807326187&sectionId=3366&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00019_195040_1517807326187
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Army and Air Force`
  line `(Disposal of Private Property) Act, 1950.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India, and applies to citizens of India and persons subject to the Army`
  line `Act, 1950 (46 of 1950), or the Air Force Act, 1950 (45 of 1950), wherever they may be.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date^1`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (3367)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00019_195040_1517807326187&sectionId=3367&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00019_195040_1517807326187
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(1) "Committee" means the Committee of Adjustment constituted under section 4;`
  line
  line `(2) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(3) "regimental and other debts in camp or quarters" includes--`
  line
  line `(i) in relation to any person subject to the Army Act, 1950 (45 of 1950), moneys due as`
  line `military debts, namely, sums due in respect of or of any advance in respect of--`
  line
  line `(a) quarters;`
  line
  line `(b) mess, band and other regimental accounts;`
  line
  line `(c) military clothing, appointments and equipments, not exceeding a sum equal to three`
  line `months' pay of the deceased and having become due within eighteen months before the date`
  line `of his death; and`
  line
  line `(ii) in relation to any person subject to the Air Force Act, 1950 (45 of 1950), moneys due as`
  line `air force debts, namely, sums due in respect of or of any advance in respect of`
  line
  line `(a) quarters;`
  line
  line `(b) mess, band and other service accounts;`
  line
  line `(c) air force clothing, appointments and equipments, not exceeding a sum equal to three`
  line `months' pay of the deceased and having become due within eighteen months before the date`
  line `of his death;`
  line
  line `(4) "representation" includes probate, letters of administration, with or without the will annexed`
  line `and a succession certificate, constituting a person executor or administrator of the estate of a deceased`
  line `person or authorising him to receive or realise the assets of a deceased person;`
  line
  line `(5) "representative" means any person who has taken out representation, but does not include an`
  line `Administrator General;`
  line
  line `(6) all words and expressions used herein and defined in the Army Act, 1950 (45 of 1950), or the`
  line `Air Force Act, 1950 (45 of 1950), and not in this Act defined shall be deemed to have the meaning`
  line `respectively attributed to them by those Acts.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (3368)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Property of deceased persons and deserters other than officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00019_195040_1517807326187&sectionId=3368&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00019_195040_1517807326187
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) On the death or desertion`
  line `of any person, not being an officer, subject to the Army Act, 1950 (45 of 1950), or the Air Force`
  line `Act, 1950 (45 of 1950), as the case may be, the commanding officer of the corps, department, detachment`
  line `or unit to which the deceased or deserter belonged, shall, as soon as may be and subject to any rules that`
  line `may be made in this behalf--`
  line
  line `(a) secure all the movable property belonging to the deceased or deserter that is in camp or`
  line `quarters, and cause an inventory thereof to be made,`
  line
  line `(b) draw the pay and allowances due to such person,`
  line
  line `(c) make due provision for the payment of regimental and other debts in camp or quarters, if any,`
  line `of such persons.`
  line
  line `(2) In the case of a deceased person, the commanding officer,--`
  line
  line `(a) if in any case not otherwise provided for by rules made under this Act it appears to him to be`
  line `necessary to make provision for the payment of regimental and other debts in camp or quarters, the`
  line `funeral expenses of the deceased and the expenses, if any, incurred by the commanding officer in`
  line `respect of the estate of the deceased, shall, and--`
  line
  line `(b) in any other case, may,--`
  line
  line `collect all moneys left by the deceased in any banking company (including any post office savings bank,`
  line `co-operative bank or society or any other institution receiving deposits in money however named) and for`
  line `that purpose may require the agent, manager or other proper officer of such banking company, society or`
  line `other institution to pay the moneys to the commanding officer forthwith, notwithstanding anything in the`
  line `rules of the banking company, society or other institution, and such agent, manager or other officer shall`
  line `be bound to comply with the requisition.`
  line
  line `(3) Where any money has been paid by a banking company, society or other institution in`
  line `compliance with a requisition made under sub-section (2), no person shall have any claim against the`
  line `banking company, society or other institution in respect of such money.`
  line
  line `(4) Where the representative of a deceased has given security to the satisfaction of the commanding`
  line `officer for the payment of the regimental and other debts in camp or quarters, if any, and of the funeral`
  line `expenses of the deceased in cases where no provision for the payment of such expenses has been made`
  line `otherwise and of the expenses, if any, incurred by the commanding officer in respect of the estate of the`
  line `deceased, the commanding officer shall deliver over the property received by him under sub-sections (1)`
  line `and (2) to that representative, whereupon his responsibility for the administration of the estate of the`
  line `deceased shall cease.`
  line
  line `(5) In the case of a deceased whose estate has not been dealt with under sub-section (4), or under`
  line `section 10, and in the case of a deserter, the commanding officer,--`
  line
  line `(i) if in any case it is necessary in his opinion so to do for the purpose of securing the payment of`
  line `the regimental and other debts in camp or quarters of the deceased or deserter, the funeral expenses of`
  line `the deceased, if any, and the expenses, if any, incurred by the commanding officer in respect of the`
  line `estate of the deceased or deserter, shall, and`
  line
  line `(ii) in any other case, may`
  line
  line `cause the movable property of the deceased or deserter, as the case may be, to be sold or converted into`
  line money.
  line
  line `(6) The commanding officer shall, out of the moneys received, collected or realised under subsections`
  line `(1), (2) and (5), pay the regimental and other debts in camp or quarters, if any, of the deceased or`
  line `deserter, as the case may be, the expenses, if any, incurred by the commanding officer in respect of the`
  line `estate of the deceased or deserter, and in the case of a deceased his funeral expenses in cases where no`
  line `provision for the payment of such expenses has been made otherwise.`
  line
  line `(7) The surplus, if any, after payment of the debts and expenses specified in sub-section (6), shall,`
  line
  line `(a) in the case of a deceased, be paid to his representative, if any, or in the event of no claim to`
  line `such surplus being established within twelve months after the death, to the prescribed person; and`
  line
  line `(b) in the case of a deserter, be forthwith paid to the prescribed person, and shall, on the expiry of`
  line `three years from the date of desertion, be forfeited to the Central Government, unless the deserter`
  line `shall have surrendered or been apprehended in the meantime:`
  line
  line `Provided that the prescribed person may, if the deserter has not surrendered or been apprehended in`
  line `the meantime, pay the whole or any part of the surplus received by him under clause (b) to the wife or`
  line `children or any other dependant of the deserter at any time during the said period of three years.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--In this section and in section 4, the word "officer" with reference to persons subject to`
  line `the Air Force Act, 1950 (45 of 1950), includes a warrant officer who has died or deserted.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (3369)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Property of officers who die or desert.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00019_195040_1517807326187&sectionId=3369&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00019_195040_1517807326187
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of section 3 shall also apply to the`
  line `disposal of the property of any officer subject to the Army Act, 1950 (45 of 1950), or the Air Force`
  line `Act, 1950 (45 of 1950), who dies or deserts, but with the following modifications, namely:--`
  line
  line `(i) the functions of the commanding officer under section 3 shall be performed by a Committee of`
  line `Adjustment constituted in this behalf in the prescribed manner;`
  line
  line `(ii) the surplus, if any, after payment of the debts and expenses specified in sub-section (6) of`
  line `section 3, shall in the case of a deceased officer, be paid to the prescribed person.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (3370)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Decision of questions as to regimental and other debts in camp or quarters.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00019_195040_1517807326187&sectionId=3370&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00019_195040_1517807326187
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `If in any case a`
  line `doubt or difference arises as to what are the regimental and other debts in camp or quarters of a deceased`
  line `or deserter or as to the amount payable in respect thereof, the decision of the prescribed person shall be`
  line `final and shall be binding on all persons for all purposes.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (3371)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Representative powers of commanding officer or Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00019_195040_1517807326187&sectionId=3371&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00019_195040_1517807326187
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `For the purpose of the exercise`
  line `of his or its duties under section 3 or section 4, the commanding officer or the Committee, as the case may`
  line `be, shall, to the exclusion of all other persons and authorities whomsoever or whatsoever, have the same`
  line `rights and powers as if he or it had taken out representation to the estate of the deceased, and any receipt`
  line `given by the commanding officer or the Committee, as the case may be, shall have effect accordingly.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (3372)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Power of Central Government to hand over estate or deceased person to the Administrator General.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00019_195040_1517807326187&sectionId=3372&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00019_195040_1517807326187
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in ^1[the Administrators-General Act, 1963`
  line `(45 of 1963)], an Administrator General shall not interpose in any manner in relation to any property of a`
  line `deceased which has been dealt with under the provisions of section 3 or section 4, except in so far as he is`
  line `expressly required or permitted to do so by or under the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may, at any time and in such circumstances as it thinks fit, direct that the`
  line `estate of a deceased shall be handed over by the commanding officer or the Committee, as the case may be, to the Administrator General of a State for administration, and thereupon the commanding officer or`
  line `the Committee, as the case may be, shall make over the estate to such Administrator General.`
  line
  line `(3) Where under this section any estate is handed over to the Administrator General, the`
  line `Administrator General shall administer such estate in accordance with the provisions of ^2[the`
  line `Administrators General Act, 1963 (45 of 1963)\, or, if that Act is not in force in any State, of the`
  line `corresponding law in force in that State:`
  line
  line `Provided that the regimental and other debts in camp or quarters of the deceased, if any, shall be paid`
  line `by the Administrator General in priority to any other debts due by the deceased.`
  line
  line `(4) The Administrator General shall pay the surplus, if any, remaining in his hands after discharging`
  line `all debts and charges, to the heirs of the deceased, and, if no heir is traceable, shall make over the surplus`
  line `in the prescribed manner to the prescribed person.`
  line
  line `(5) The Administrator General shall not charge in respect of his duties under this section any fee`
  line `exceeding three per cent. of the gross amount coming to or remaining in his hands after payment of the`
  line `regimental and other debts in camp or quarters.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 31 of 2000, s. 2, for "the Administrator General's Act ,1913 (3 of 1913)" (w.e.f. 25-8-2000).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 31 of 2000, s. 2, for "the Administrator General's Act, 1913 (3 of 1913)" (w.e.f. 25-8-2000).`
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (3373)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Disposal of surplus by prescribed persons.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00019_195040_1517807326187&sectionId=3373&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00019_195040_1517807326187
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `On receipt of the surplus referred to in sub-section`
  line `(7) of section 3 or clause (ii) of section 4 or sub-section (4) of section 7, the prescribed person shall,--`
  line
  line `(a) if he knows of a representative of the deceased, pay the surplus to that representative;`
  line
  line `(b) if he does not know of any such representative and the surplus has not been disposed of under`
  line `section 10, publish every year a notice in the prescribed form and manner for six consecutive years`
  line `and if no claim to the surplus is made by a representative of the deceased within six months even after`
  line `the publication of the last of such notices, the prescribed person shall deposit the surplus together with`
  line `any income or accumulation of income accrued therefrom to the credit of the Central Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that such deposit shall not bar the claim of any person to such surplus or any part thereof, if`
  line `he is otherwise entitled to it.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (3374)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Disposal of effects, not money.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00019_195040_1517807326187&sectionId=3374&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00019_195040_1517807326187
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `Where any part of the estate of a deceased person consists of`
  line `effects, securities or other property not converted into money, the provisions of sub-section (7) of section`
  line `3, clause (ii) of section 4 and section 8, with respect to the payment of the surplus, shall, save as may be`
  line `prescribed, extend to the delivery, transmission or transfer of such effects, securities or property, and the`
  line `prescribed person shall have the same power of converting the same into money as a representative of the`
  line deceased.
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (3375)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Disposal of certain property without production of probate, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for "ten thousand" (w.e.f. 25-8-2000).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00019_195040_1517807326187&sectionId=3375&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00019_195040_1517807326187
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `Property deliverable and`
  line `money payable to the representative of a deceased under section 3 or section 4 or section 8 may, if the`
  line `total amount or value thereof does not exceed ^1[two lakhs] rupees and if the prescribed person thinks fit,`
  line `be delivered or paid to any person appearing to him to be entitled to receive it or to administer the estate`
  line `of the deceased without requiring such person to produce any probate, letters of administration,`
  line `succession certificate or other such conclusive evidence of title.`
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (3376)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Discharge of commanding officer, Committee, prescribed person and the Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00019_195040_1517807326187&sectionId=3376&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00019_195040_1517807326187
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `Any payment or application of money or application, delivery, sale or other disposition`
  line `of any property made, or purported to be made, by the commanding officer, the Committee or the`
  line `prescribed person in good faith in pursuance of section 3, section 4, section 8, section 9 or section 10 shall be valid and shall be a full discharge to the commanding officer, the Committee or the prescribed person,`
  line `as the case may be, and to the Central Government from all further liability in respect of that money of`
  line `property; but nothing herein contained shall affect the right of any executor or administrator or other`
  line `representative, or of any creditor of the deceased against any person to whom such payment or delivery`
  line `has been made.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (3377)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Property in the hands of commanding officer, Committee or prescribed person not to be assets where commanding officer, Committee or prescribed person is stationed.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00019_195040_1517807326187&sectionId=3377&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00019_195040_1517807326187
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `Any property`
  line `coming into the hands of the commanding officer or the Committee or the prescribed person under section`
  line `3, section 4 or sub-section (4) of section 7 shall not, by reason thereof, be deemed to be assets of effects at`
  line `the place in which that commanding officer or the Committee or the prescribed persons is stationed, and it`
  line `shall not be necessary by reason thereof that representation be taken out in respect of that property for that`
  line place.
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (3378)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Saving of rights of representative.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00019_195040_1517807326187&sectionId=3378&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00019_195040_1517807326187
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `After the commanding officer, or the Committee has paid`
  line `to the prescribed person the surplus of the property of any deceased under sub-section (7) of section 3 or`
  line `clause (ii) of section 4, any representative of the deceased or any Administrator General, shall, as regards`
  line `any property of the deceased not collected by the commanding officer or the Committee, as the case may`
  line `be, and not forming part of the aforesaid surplus, have the same rights and duties as if sections 3 and 4`
  line `had not been enacted.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (3379)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Application of sections 3 to 13 to persons of unsound mind or to persons reported missing on active service.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 31 of 2000, s. 4, for "the Indian Lunacy Act, 1912 (4 of 1912)" (w.e.f. 25-8-2000).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00019_195040_1517807326187&sectionId=3379&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00019_195040_1517807326187
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of sections 3 to 13 shall, so far as they can be made applicable, also`
  line `apply in the case of a person subject to the Army Act, 1950 (45 of 1950), or the Air Force Act, 1950`
  line `(45 of 1950), as the case may be, who, notwithstanding anything contained ^1[the Mental Health Act, 1987`
  line `(14 of 1987)], is ascertained in the prescribed manner to be of unsound mind, or who, while on active`
  line `service, is officially reported missing, as if he had died on the day on which his unsoundness of mind is so`
  line `ascertained or, as the case may be, on the day on which he is officially reported missing:`
  line
  line `Provided that in the case of a person so reported missing, no action shall be taken under`
  line `sub-section (2) to (6) or section 3 or section 4 or section 7 until such time as he is officially presumed to`
  line `be dead.`
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (3380)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Appointment of standing Committee of Adjustment in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00019_195040_1517807326187&sectionId=3380&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00019_195040_1517807326187
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `When an officer dies`
  line `or deserts or is ascertained in the prescribed manner to be of unsound mind or while on active service is`
  line `officially reported missing, the references in the foregoing provisions of this Act to the Committee shall`
  line `be construed as references to the Standing Committee of Adjustment, if any, constituted in this behalf in`
  line `the prescribed manner and such Standing Committee shall alone be entitled to perform all the functions of`
  line `the Committee under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (3381)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00019_195040_1517807326187&sectionId=3381&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00019_195040_1517807326187
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `make rules^1`
  line `for the purpose of carrying into effect the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may--`
  line
  line `(a) prescribe the manner in which any property belonging to a deceased or deserter may be`
  line `secured or collected and his regimental and other debts in camp or quarters paid;`
  line
  line `(b) provide for the payment of the funeral expenses of any deceased;`
  line
  line `(c) provide for the constitution of the Committee of Adjustment or any Standing Committee of`
  line `Adjustment under this Act;`
  line
  line `(d) specify the person who shall be regarded as the prescribed person for the purposes of this Act;`
  line
  line `(e) prescribe the circumstances in which the estate of any deceased shall be handed over to the`
  line `Administrator General;`
  line
  line `(f) prescribe the form and manner in which a notice under section 8 shall be published;`
  line
  line `(g) prescribe the procedure by which any person may be ascertained to be of unsound mind.`
  line
  line `^2[(3) Every rule made by the Central Government under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after`
  line `it is made, before each House of Parliament while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which`
  line `may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the`
  line `session immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in`
  line `making any modification in the rule or both houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall`
  line `thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that`
  line `any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done`
  line `under that rule.]`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 20 of 1983, s. 2, and the Schedule (w.e.f. 15-3-1984).`
  line
  line `2. For the Army and Air Force (Disposal of Private Property) Rules, 1953, see Gazette of India, 1953, Part II, s. 4.`
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (3382)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title Repealed.
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00019_195040_1517807326187&sectionId=3382&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00019_195040_1517807326187
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `[Repeals.]--Rep. by the Repealing and Amending Act, 1957 (36 of 1957), s. 2 and the`
  line `First Schedule.`
